The paper discusses the non-determinism in execution environments and its potential impact on safety-related systems. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the activation of residual systematic faults in software, which is a concern in safety-critical systems, indicating a connection to systems and control (cs.SY) and operating systems (cs.OS).
